Several zooecia in this colony display regeneration features, some of which have an intact skeleton, but a second or even third orifice implanted in the primary one. This suggests that these zooids were fed upon by a partial predator, possibly a nudibranch gastropod boring through the operculum and sucking out the internal organs without damaging the skeleton (e.g. 
McKinney, Taylor & Lidgard, 2003
), after which a new zooid – an intramural bud (see 
Taylor, 1988b
) – was produced within the older one.
